tip.text: There's all sorts of activities you can do here. From single cycling, tandem cycling, trishaw cycling, BBQ, camping to roller blading. There's also a place for prawning.

formattedAddress: Along East Coast Pkwy (East Coast Park Service Rd)

tip.text: Roof top green grass. Good for family picnics as well as dates! You can even fly your kites. If you don't have one, you can always purchase them from the shop downstairs.
Long queue as usual. If you like sweet and spicy sambas, then this is a place for you! Comes with variety choices of dishes as well as their famous fried chicken wings.
Three stories high shop lot serving only Korean dessert. The patbingsu was just ok.. Always crowded. There's an outdoor seating too.
Nice huge rooms. Affordable price too. A little far from the mrt but you can take the bus if you're too lazy to walk. There's a bbq pit area for barbecuing too!

venue.name: CATS Cafe JB - Cats At Their Sanctuary

tip.text: I love the ambience, decor and coffee! Love that they have plenty of unique coffees. A little on the expensive side though.

tip.text: Yummy BBQ meat with 15 different type of refillable side dishes. Free tea and ice cream potong. All was good except the pancake should be crispier!
Guilin, China lookalike. Small park will huge wow-ness. Suitable just for picture taking. Not much you can do there though. It's a shame there's no direct bus service too.
I don't understand why people would hate this place. It's beautiful! Spectacular sceneries.. Cute wild boars eating durian.. Spotted a few good dating spots too!
Tried their fusion laksa pesto spaghetti. A unique combination of Asian Peranakan and Italian. It blends really well together. Perhaps, could be spicier?

tip.text: Most of the exhibition halls are closed for renovation until Sept 2015. Nothing much to see when I went there in June 2015. However, they do have lots of activities to keep the children entertained.
